  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prepositioning and Distribution of Critical Winterization Support for Most Vulnerable Communities in the Eastern Conflict Area of Ukraine</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Almost eight years after the onset of the crisis in eastern Ukraine, the conflict continues at an overall low intensity on both sides of the Line of Contact (LoC) that separates the Government-Controlled Areas (GCA) and the Non-Government-Controlled Areas (NGCA). While the overall situation has slightly improved in the GCA since the beginning of the conflict, pockets of poverty and extreme needs remain all along the LoC, compounded by an overall dysfunctional, ill equipped and poorly funded system for provision of essential services. Through this grant, IOM is receiving and prepositioning high thermal blankets for three months in Kyiv, part of USAID&#x2019;s Bureau of Humanitarian Assistant (BHA) in-kind donation. In case of rapid onset crises, in coordination with local authorities and relevant humanitarian actors through the Shelter/NFIs Cluster and its Winterization Working Group, IOM will use the blanket stocks to readily deliver essential winterization assistance to displaced families and/or other conflict-affected households and individuals in need.</narrative>
  </description>
